The Lagniappe Arcana: Combined Guidebook
FRONT MATTER
Opening Invocation
Lagniappe Tarot is a deck shaped by the rituals, histories, and everyday magic of New Orleans, offering grounded interpretations that honor the lineages that shaped the city.
A Note on Lineage: This deck references the profound historical currents of Louisiana Voudou and root work that saturate the city's psychic landscape. These systems belong strictly to the lineages and communities of color that preserved them through centuries of resistance. For an outside practitioner, working with this deck requires approaching these symbols not as an exotic aesthetic to exploit or appropriate, but with deep respect for their historical reality, absolute privacy, and structural authority.
How to Use the Deck
This guidebook provides grounded interpretations localized to the New Orleans psychic landscape. Each card entry unifies historical lore with practical domain meanings across Love, Work, Community, Self, and Spirit to provide absolute clarity.
When reading, Upright positions indicate applied intention, authority, and crossing thresholds. Reversed positions indicate the Shadow: a refusal to engage, deceit, or a catastrophic loss of control. Pay close attention to the Environmental Tells—sudden sensory cues in your surroundings that anchor the card's energy in material reality.
